    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, with 2 tbsp<span class=\"text-danger\"> [4 tbsp]</span> <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add half the<strong> yellow mustard seeds</strong> (save the rest for later!) and cook for 10 sec or until they're beginning to pop</p>\r\n<p>Once popping, add the<strong> ground fenugreek</strong>, <strong>ground black pepper</strong> and the <strong>basil leaves</strong> and cook for 10 sec&nbsp;further</p>",
